for general audiences he has written nine books including the new york times bestselling the warren buffett way and the warren buffett portfolio mastering the power of the focus investment strategy robert is a graduate of villanova university with a ba and ma and is a chartered financial analyst he lives with his family in villanova pennsylvania visit roberts website at httproberthagstromcom read full biography master the skills that made warren buffett the worlds greatest investor the warren buffett way rd edition a new york times bestseller — over  million sold by robert g hagstrom  better than ever the third edition of the warren buffett way explains the timeless principles and strategies that made warren buffett the greatest investor of our time drawing on ideas from behavioral finance the new edition shows how investors can master the challenges of longterm investing and in so doing more closely emulate the buffett way of investing highlights include how buffett combines the best of value and growth investing analysis of buffetts most important and most recent investments how buffetts behavioral analytical and organizational edge allows him to outperform other investors the number one book on buffetts methods the warren buffett way third edition provides a roadmap for mastering the stock selection and psychological skills that are the foundation of buffetts success the warren buffett way workbook by robert g hagstrom russell rhoads  the warren buffett way workbook consists of over  questions and answers to help readers of the warren buffett way test and further develop their knowledge of buffetts hugely successful investment approach the workbook follows the warren buffett way third edition providing a combination of multiplechoice and essay questions for each chapter in the core book highlights include buying a business case studies on buffetts most important stock purchases the mathematics of investing the perfect accompaniment to the warren buffett way third edition and the warren buffett way video course the workbook will provide readers with a sure path to begin investing just like warren buffett the warren buffett way video course by robert g hagstrom  narrated by the warren buffett way author robert g hagstrom the warren buffett way video course is an eloquent and inspiring presentation of buffetts methods and how they can be applied by other investors hagstrom traces buffett from his childhood to today describing his intellectual influences and the evolution of his investing strategies highlights include what buffett learned from ben graham phil fisher and charlie munger buffetts twelve immutable tenets for selecting stocks how behavioral finance lends insights into buffetts success and how those insights can be used by individual investors the minute video will serve as a great introduction to buffett for new investors and will help others already acquainted with buffett to reinforce and better apply their knowledge sample video clips by john wiley  sons inc or related companies all rights reserved please read our privacy policy warren buffett  wikipedia warren buffett from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search warren buffett warren buffett in  born warren edward buffett  august   age  omaha nebraska us residence omaha nebraska us alma mater university of pennsylvania transferred university of nebraska–lincoln bs columbia university ms occupation investor business magnate and philanthropist years active –present known for leadership of berkshire hathaway with charlie munger salary us net worth us billion may  spouses susan thompson m  her death  astrid menks m  children susan alice buffett howard graham buffett peter buffett parents howard buffett leila stahl buffett relatives howard warren buffett grandson signature warren edward buffett ˈbʌfᵻt born august   is an american business magnate investor and philanthropist he is considered by some to be one of the most successful investors in the world and as of march  is the second wealthiest person in the united states and the fourth wealthiest in the world with a total net worth of  billion born in omaha buffett developed an interest in business and investing in his youth eventually entering the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania in  before transferring and graduating from university of nebraska–lincoln at the age of  buffett went on to enroll and graduate from columbia university where he learned and eventually molded his investment philosophy around a concept pioneered by benjamin graham–value investing he attended new york institute of finance to specialize his economics background and soon after began various business partnerships including one with graham after meeting charlie munger buffett created the buffett partnership his firm would eventually acquire a textile manufacturing firm called berkshire hathaway and assume its name to create a diversified holding company buffett has been the chairman and largest shareholder of berkshire hathaway since  and his business exploits have had him referred to as the wizard oracle or sage of omaha by global media outlets he is noted for his adherence to value investing and for his personal frugality despite his immense wealth buffett is a notable philanthropist having pledged to give away  percent of his fortune to philanthropic causes primarily via the bill  melinda gates foundation in  with bill gates and mark zuckerberg warren founded the giving pledge whereby billionaires pledge to give away at least half of their fortunes he is also active in contributing to political causes having endorsed democratic candidate hillary clinton in the  us presidential election he has publicly opposed the policies actions and statements of the current us president donald trump contents  early life and education  investment career  early business career  assuming berkshire  as a billionaire   financial crisis  a capitalized berkshire  investment philosophy  inde